cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.SI 

The paper introduces a novel evolutionary algorithm for computational creativity that uses semantic networks and employs commonsense reasoning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper also introduces a fitness measure that is computed through structure mapping, which is a technique commonly used in Computational Creativity (cs.CC) research. Finally, the paper's focus on open-ended generation of networks suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
